   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# End-to-End Walkthrough\n",
    "\n",
    "Runs the full RAG pipeline with assertions at each layer: retrieval correctness (Layer 3), generation with abstention (Layer 4), and hallucination guard edge cases (Layer 5)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "7328c879",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "%run notebook_init.py\n",
    "\n",
    "from rag_pipeline.retriever.retrieve import query_chunks\n",
    "from rag_pipeline.llm.generator import generate_answer_with_gate"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b1c2d3e4-layer3",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Layer 3: Retrieval Pipeline\n",
    "\n",
    "Verifies that the hybrid retrieval returns relevant chunks for known query types and handles nonsense gracefully."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "3aaa0861",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Test 1: Location query (should hit ITEM 2 / Properties)\n",
    "chunks = query_chunks(\"Where is Tesla headquartered?\", top_k=5)\n",
    "assert len(chunks) > 0, \"No chunks returned\"\n",
    "assert all(\"text\" in c and \"metadata\" in c for c in chunks), \"Chunks missing fields\"\n",
    "print(f\"Test 1 passed: {len(chunks)} chunks returned\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Test 2: Risk query (should hit ITEM 1A)\n",
    "chunks = query_chunks(\"What are Tesla's main risk factors?\", top_k=5)\n",
    "assert any(\"1A\" in c[\"metadata\"].get(\"section\", \"\").upper() or \"RISK\" in c[\"metadata\"].get(\"section\", \"\").upper() for c in chunks), \"Risk query didn't retrieve risk section\"\n",
    "print(f\"Test 2 passed: risk sections found\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Test 3: Nonsense query (should still return chunks, not crash)\n",
    "chunks = query_chunks(\"asdfghjkl\", top_k=5)\n",
    "print(f\"Test 3 passed: nonsense query returned {len(chunks)} chunks without error\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c2d3e4f5-layer4",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Layer 4: Generation Pipeline\n",
    "\n",
    "Tests end-to-end answer generation: a factual query should produce a cited answer, a nonsense query should trigger abstention."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "3df949aa",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Test 1: Factual query should produce an answer\n",
    "chunks = query_chunks(\"Where is Tesla headquartered?\", top_k=5)\n",
    "answer, abstained = generate_answer_with_gate(\"Where is Tesla headquartered?\", chunks)\n",
    "print(f\"Answer: {answer}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Abstained: {abstained}\")\n",
    "assert not abstained, f\"Should not have abstained, got: {answer}\"\n",
    "print(\"Test 1 passed: factual query answered\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Test 2: Nonsense query — expect abstention (depends on LLM behavior)\n",
    "chunks = query_chunks(\"asdfghjkl\", top_k=5)\n",
    "answer, abstained = generate_answer_with_gate(\"asdfghjkl\", chunks)\n",
    "print(f\"\\nAnswer: {answer}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Abstained: {abstained}\")\n",
    "if abstained:\n",
    "    print(\"Test 2 passed: nonsense query correctly abstained\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"Test 2 warning: nonsense query was not abstained — LLM may have hallucinated\")""
   ]
  }
 ],
